1. Write a program in which you would have an integer array of size 10.
Fill out 6 values into this array, using pointer concept.
Display the array .

2. Write a program in which you have an integer array with 10 numbers.
Fetch the values using pointer and display the same.

3. Have an array of 10 integers. Take two inputs from the user, namely
position1 and position2. Now swap the values at position1 and 2 of the array.
Display original array and final array. 

4. Achieve(3) using pointers.

5. Arrange an array of integers in ascending order using pointer concept.
